      <dsc>
         <c id="ref10" level="series">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Letters and Documents</unittitle>
            </did>
            <c id="ref11" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Bailly de Fresnay, Charles Gaspart, Elisabeth Joseph, Marquis de, 1765-1850</unittitle>
               </did>
               <c id="ref12" level="file">
                  <did>
                     <unittitle>ALS (in French) to [Sir David Dundas?], Wildsgemsen</unittitle>
                     <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1795 Mar 30</unitdate>
                     <container containerid="39002099370513"
                                id="aspace_e2f08e0577f512e0abcc091ec20fb3f1"
                                label="Mixed Materials"
                                localtype="box">1</container>
                     <container id="aspace_a0dcb3bba00c71076ffe6be0d5fb4576"
                                localtype="folder"
                                parent="aspace_e2f08e0577f512e0abcc091ec20fb3f1">1</container>
                  </did>
                  <scopecontent id="aspace_5c3892a573e2046188191f1738404493">
                     <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                     <p>Reports on his activities including an unfortunate incident in which a fight broke out between a detachment of his troops and some peasants.</p>
                  </scopecontent>
               </c>
               <c id="ref14" level="file">
                  <did>
                     <unittitle>ALS in (French) to unnamed recipient, Otterburg</unittitle>
                     <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1795 Apr 4</unitdate>
                     <container containerid="39002099370513"
                                id="aspace_1770b14592994a6098b937e12acf517f"
                                label="Mixed Materials"
                                localtype="box">1</container>
                     <container id="aspace_fa1208c33aef06c8ba35fd2282931e2d"
                                localtype="folder"
                                parent="aspace_1770b14592994a6098b937e12acf517f">2</container>
                  </did>
                  <scopecontent id="aspace_19360e157445f284faa6ac4b1f9440c4">
                     <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                     <p>Informs the recipient that he has been put in charge of transporting rations and supplies from Otterburg to Bremen.</p>
                  </scopecontent>
               </c>
               <c id="ref16" level="file">
                  <did>
                     <unittitle>ALS (in French) to unnamed recipient, [n.p.]</unittitle>
                     <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">n.d.</unitdate>
                     <container containerid="39002099370513"
                                id="aspace_29d5ab06d43d292752b397e714f4940c"
                                label="Mixed Materials"
                                localtype="box">1</container>
                     <container id="aspace_ef54b9b145f134c6aa1568a6c37a32d4"
                                localtype="folder"
                                parent="aspace_29d5ab06d43d292752b397e714f4940c">3</container>
                  </did>
                  <scopecontent id="aspace_c29f38a7333428bdab437a3a1a1ee77c">
                     <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                     <p>Concerns problems with his troops.</p>
                  </scopecontent>
               </c>
            </c>
            <c id="ref18" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Bentinck, Lord William Cavendish, 1774-1839</unittitle>
               </did>
               <c id="ref19" level="file">
                  <did>
                     <unittitle>ALS (in French) to Sir George Don, Nienburg</unittitle>
                     <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1796 May 13</unitdate>
                     <container containerid="39002099370513"
                                id="aspace_615b6231cbbbaabf3eb6dd8500b94292"
                                label="Mixed Materials"
                                localtype="box">1</container>
                     <container id="aspace_6d200bc420d1254fc0acfe75a949cfd2"
                                localtype="folder"
                                parent="aspace_615b6231cbbbaabf3eb6dd8500b94292">4</container>
                  </did>
                  <scopecontent id="aspace_d5a87c9f4b8a883aea3c55dc2e7fba24">
                     <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                     <p>Concerns the embarrassing problem of being able to pay officers only half what they are due. Asks Don to send him some money on account.</p>
                  </scopecontent>
               </c>
               <c id="ref21" level="file">
                  <did>
                     <unittitle>Letter (copy, in French) to Captain Nacquart, Nienburg</unittitle>
                     <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1795 Nov 19</unitdate>
                     <container containerid="39002099370513"
                                id="aspace_8961ed6c48d45a19f82ccacd93eb4429"
                                label="Mixed Materials"
                                localtype="box">1</container>
                     <container id="aspace_09ee1f51343b166feee892ef3b1b5426"
                                localtype="folder"
                                parent="aspace_8961ed6c48d45a19f82ccacd93eb4429">5</container>
                  </did>
                  <scopecontent id="aspace_22d325b5c93f2b1c2ab7f2a6151ffb5a">
                     <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                     <p>Concerns problems of coordination in strategy between the British High Command and her Dutch allies.</p>
                  </scopecontent>
               </c>
               <c id="ref23" level="file">
                  <did>
                     <unittitle>ALS (in French) to unnamed recipient, Bremen</unittitle>
                     <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1796 Jan 9</unitdate>
                     <container containerid="39002099370513"
                                id="aspace_af575b1a7902d3d9c35c0b094ed1049d"
                                label="Mixed Materials"
                                localtype="box">1</container>
                     <container id="aspace_7997f277e0d2646f542dd16611768bcd"
                                localtype="folder"
                                parent="aspace_af575b1a7902d3d9c35c0b094ed1049d">6</container>
                  </did>
                  <scopecontent id="aspace_26bdf807e3242460cddc4ea35655c709">
                     <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                     <p>Sends the names of 13 French officers who want to join the British Army.</p>
                  </scopecontent>
               </c>
            </c>
            <c id="ref25" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Béthisy de Mézières, Richard Henri Charles de, 1770-1827. ALS (in French) to unnamed recipient, Salzburg</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1795 Mar 16</unitdate>
                  <container containerid="39002099370513"
                             id="aspace_fc9aa021ecae9b87dcdc630f1928effe"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">1</container>
                  <container id="aspace_a66338790fb25b96981998c5688d3c3b"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_fc9aa021ecae9b87dcdc630f1928effe">7</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_dd45ebb10d427cc01494838cd98cac0c">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>From the commander of an advances outpost to his superior pleading for the relief of his squadron.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="ref27" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Brownrigg, Sir Robert, 1759-1833. ALS to Sir George Don, [n.p.]</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">[n.y.] Mar 21</unitdate>
                  <container containerid="39002099370513"
                             id="aspace_d5d3331d15d3dd8d793507ccecb34ebc"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">1</container>
                  <container id="aspace_a30fc4c00a772d019137404f604efdf1"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_d5d3331d15d3dd8d793507ccecb34ebc">8</container>
               </did>
            </c>
            <c id="ref28" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Choiseul Stainville, Antoine Clériadus Gabriel, Duc de, 1760-1838. LS (in secretary's hand, in French) to Frederick Augustus, Duke of York, Driel</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1794 Sep 4</unitdate>
                  <container containerid="39002099370513"
                             id="aspace_2850ca1e598b5dd540c90ffb0f247d7f"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">1</container>
                  <container id="aspace_76b0219af2b95ee022173e64edaa8f83"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_2850ca1e598b5dd540c90ffb0f247d7f">9</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_7ead83cf06c39b3ae3aced4dbd161fa6">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Asks permission to raise a fourth squadron of his regiment. The cost would be 30 louis per man fully equipped and mounted.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="ref30" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>De la Porte, Mr. ALS (in French) to Sir David Dundas, Bremen</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1795 Jun 2</unitdate>
                  <container containerid="39002099370513"
                             id="aspace_04d7906dafd30043405adad2a5312fce"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">1</container>
                  <container id="aspace_b7a87290e01d83e893e8385b2c371ca4"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_04d7906dafd30043405adad2a5312fce">10</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_012622914b99801b320543f1883d1230">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Asks that General Dundas will see fit to arrange passages to England for those French gentlemen who wish to serve under British Command.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="ref32" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Dundas, Sir David, 1735-1820. ALS to Sir George Don, Lingen</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">[ca. 1795] Feb 28</unitdate>
                  <container containerid="39002099370513"
                             id="aspace_be6282696ec0a21d173d1fa2185193f7"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">1</container>
                  <container id="aspace_60719a026f97629a18c768337978c9fe"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_be6282696ec0a21d173d1fa2185193f7">11</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_f6738ac68d565a01966bc489a37ce534">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Concerns communication and logistic problems for the English army operating against the French in the Netherlands.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="ref34" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Durell, Thomas. "List of captive French prisoners to be exchanged" (holograph, signed), Hoxter</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1795 Aug 26</unitdate>
                  <container containerid="39002099370513"
                             id="aspace_670a93ef4bd8fd7a3ef512ac6b0a499c"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">1</container>
                  <container id="aspace_4b679fc8994ad266fae7ad5714710aef"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_670a93ef4bd8fd7a3ef512ac6b0a499c">12</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_33253e7c214b419e73d08d0c44ebbb4e">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Includes their rank, date of capture, and regiment.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="ref36" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Harcourt, William Harcourt, 3d Earl, 1743-1830. ALS (in French) to Mr. Duhon, Bremen</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1792 Apr 2</unitdate>
                  <container containerid="39002099370513"
                             id="aspace_68d92f1e67f5169e70169e98277163a6"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">1</container>
                  <container id="aspace_765da87115859e0381ff09cb588cb1d5"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_68d92f1e67f5169e70169e98277163a6">13</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_57f736bcc9b1db1d972dde8d212d1f06">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Warns Duhon that he is responsible for detachment having requisitioned food from civilians.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="ref38" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Kielmansegge, Comte de. Letter (copy, in French) to Lord William Bentinck, Hanover</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1795, Dec 23</unitdate>
                  <container containerid="39002099370513"
                             id="aspace_095471d46bd97f985fdc17941ea6dd86"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">1</container>
                  <container id="aspace_41c4ceab7b9d98f088b59feb07318580"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_095471d46bd97f985fdc17941ea6dd86">14</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_adebedc9a0bdd88915a5fd3835d022c5">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Reports "les etats allemands de La Majestie" do not want expatriate Dutch soldiers on their territory.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="ref40" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Menu, H., abbé. ALS (in French) to unnamed recipient, Minden</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1795 Mar 1</unitdate>
                  <container containerid="39002099370513"
                             id="aspace_6b84cb3fe8a34742433ef9cfc187a299"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">1</container>
                  <container id="aspace_1e48b7c30043e1d963eff9eb27861655"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_6b84cb3fe8a34742433ef9cfc187a299">15</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_c0e6b77029ef528a2f8a6b13a23a58c0">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Concerns a messenger sent to Menu from the recipient, a colonel.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="ref42" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Mozane, Cananas du. 2 ALS (in French) to Sir James Henry Craig, [v.p.]</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1794 Jul 17, Nov 8</unitdate>
                  <container containerid="39002099370513"
                             id="aspace_a558c29022369e927b145219688fa481"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">1</container>
                  <container id="aspace_87e4766e3581b4b9ccc7cae3ec35161c"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_a558c29022369e927b145219688fa481">16</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_987334572ef0b6d17889db1c4fcc7e8a">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>The first letter suggests the extension of an amnesty to those French soldiers willing to desert the British. The second reports on the progress of their programs and includes descriptions of specific cases of desertions.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
         </c>
